==English==
{{Wikipedia}}
===Etymology===
From [[Old French]] ''[[blason]]'' "shield".

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/ˈbleɪzən/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{heraldry}}: A verbal or written description of a [[coat of arms]].
#:'''Quotations'''
#:* '''1894''': ...it should never be forgotten that the best '''blazon''' is that which is the most perspicuous &mdash; James Parker, ''A Glossary of Terms Used in Heraldry''.
# {{heraldry}}: A formalized [[language]] for describing a [[coat of arms]].
#:'''Quotations'''
#:* '''1997''': We must banish, therefore, the persistent but wholly erroneous notion that the heralds ''invented'' many of the terms used in '''blazon''' and borrowed the rest from the ''everyday'' lexicon of terms... &mdash; Gerard J. Brault, ''Early Blazon''
# {{heraldry}}: A [[coat of arms]] or a [[banner]] depicting a coat of arms.

